'''Tarisian ale''' was an extremely strong [[Alcohol/Legends|alcoholic]] beverage brewed on [[Taris/Legends|Taris]]. It was one of the [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] main exports. The [[Ale/Legends|ale]] was made from the glands of a [[Tach/Legends|tach]], and because of the need for tach gland, there were substantial imports of tach glands from [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]]. Consuming just one was enough to intoxicate, or even incapacitate, inexperienced drinkers or even experienced drinkers who were having their first Tarisian ale.

Perhaps for that reason, it was popular amongst the [[Darth Revan's Sith Empire|Sith]] troops who occupied Taris during the [[Jedi Civil War]]. Many of the Sith that purchased this drink may have used it as a way to forget the pressures of Sith life at the barracks in the [[Tarisian military base]], which was described as "boring" by several of the Sith stationed there.

The drink ceased to be produced after the planetary bombardment of Taris in [[3956 BBY]], due to the fact that few off-worlders knew how to make it, although [[Griff Vao]] claimed to have the recipe, and hoped to monopolize the drink after Taris was destroyed.

By the year [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], Tarisian ale had made a comeback, being served at the [[Horizon Hotel]] in the [[Upper City]]. Patrons, such as the veteran [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] [[Soldier/Legends|soldier]] [[Goran Beviin]], could order mugs of Tarisian ale at the [[Hotel/Legends|hotel]] bar, in addition to bowls of [[deep-fried coin-crabs]].<ref name="Bloodlines">''[[Legacy of the Force: Bloodlines]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Tarisian ale was first introduced to the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe via a mention in [[BioWare]]'s [[2003]] role-playing [[Star Wars video games|video game]], ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'',<ref name="KOTOR">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref> before later appearing in full in "[[Shadows and Light]]," a [[2005]] story published in the [[Star Wars Tales 23|twenty-third]] issue of the ''[[Star Wars Tales]]'' [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series.<ref name="ShadowsandLight">{{Tales|23|Shadows and Light}}</ref> Tarisian ale appeared again in the second entry in the multi-[[Author/Legends|author]] ''[[Star Wars: Legacy of the Force]]'' novel series, [[Legacy of the Force: Bloodlines|''Bloodlines'']], written by [[Karen Traviss]] and published [[August 29]], [[2006]].<ref name="Bloodlines" />

